Class StartBuildActivityTask

java.lang.Object
  Task
      com.ibm.team.build.ant.task.AbstractTeamBuildTask
          com.ibm.team.build.ant.task.AbstractPublisherTask
              com.ibm.team.build.ant.task.StartBuildActivityTask

public class StartBuildActivityTask
extends AbstractPublisherTask

Ant task for starting a new build activity. Build may have multiple activities in progress at any time.

Activities may be hierarchical, specifying an existing parent activity when they are started.

Activities may be explicitly completed using the completeBuildActivity task, or they may be set to automatically complete by specifying autoComplete=true. In this case the activity is automatically completed when either the build is completed, its parent activity is completed or when the next peer activity is started.

Required attributes are:

  • label - Describes the build activity.

Optional attributes are:

  • activityIdProperty - The ant property in which to store the unique id of the newly started activity. Only necessary if the caller intends to explicitly complete this activity using the completeBuildActivity task or if this activity will be used as a parent for child activities.
  • parentActivityId - The id of an already started activity to be the parent of this one. An activity with this id must exist and must not be already completed.
  • autoComplete - Whether or not this activity should be automatically completed when either the build is completed, a parent activity is completed or when the next peer activity is started. Defaults to false.
See AbstractPublisherTask for additional required and optional attributes.

Since:
0.5
